00:33:20.990 --> 00:33:22.290
&gt;&gt; Margaret Barker: Nyjer seed.

00:33:22.290 --> 00:33:26.140
Nyjer seed is not thistle seed.

00:33:26.140 --> 00:33:28.720
Branding it thistle is marketing.

00:33:28.720 --> 00:33:31.860
Maybe because gold
finches look really good

00:33:31.860 --> 00:33:34.420
on purple flowers, I don't know.

00:33:34.420 --> 00:33:39.080
The spelling was changed
to N-y-j-e-r

00:33:39.080 --> 00:33:42.230
to avoid pronunciation
of a racial epithet.

00:33:42.230 --> 00:33:48.160
Alfred Martin's 1963 book, "Hand
Taming Wild Birds at the Feeder,"

00:33:48.160 --> 00:33:51.720
described feeding Nyjer,
a caged bird seed

00:33:51.720 --> 00:33:54.780
at the time, to his
backyard finches.

00:33:54.780 --> 00:34:01.880
And he said, and he said in print
that, "They absolutely loved it."

00:34:01.880 --> 00:34:06.110
So Nyjer was first imported
for wild birds a few years

00:34:06.110 --> 00:34:08.320
after Martin's book.

00:34:08.320 --> 00:34:12.380
It comes mostly from Ethiopia
and India where it is grown

00:34:12.380 --> 00:34:16.720
for cooking oil, and the
cage, and wild bird markets.

00:34:16.720 --> 00:34:20.940
It is heat treated for not just
weeds when it enters the U.S., and,

00:34:20.940 --> 00:34:27.210
in fact, up in Baltimore there
is a small sterilization plant.

00:34:27.210 --> 00:34:31.230
Maryland ornithologist -- some
of you might have known him,

00:34:31.230 --> 00:34:34.120
John Dennis, promoted bird feeding.

00:34:34.120 --> 00:34:38.500
And he promoted feeding
Nyjer in his 1975 book,

00:34:38.500 --> 00:34:41.660
"A Complete Guide to Bird Feeding."

00:34:41.660 --> 00:34:47.960
And he clearly states there
that Nyjer is not thistle.

00:34:51.090 --> 00:34:54.340
Recently many of us have
put up hummingbird feeders

00:34:54.340 --> 00:34:58.340
because the hummers are back.

00:34:58.340 --> 00:35:02.880
It has taken decades to
develop hummingbird feeders

00:35:02.880 --> 00:35:06.770
and sugar water recipes
we use today.

00:35:06.770 --> 00:35:10.780
Early feeding accounts include
one about John James Audubon

00:35:10.780 --> 00:35:15.460
at a Louisiana plantation in
1821 watching hummingbirds

00:35:15.460 --> 00:35:18.680
at flowers filled with
sweetened wine.

00:35:18.680 --> 00:35:23.350
An 1899 "Bird Lore" article
describes Clark University

00:35:23.350 --> 00:35:27.140
professor, Clifton Hodge,
entertaining his students

00:35:27.140 --> 00:35:30.990
by attracting a hummer to flowers
he had sprinkled with honey

00:35:30.990 --> 00:35:34.130
and hidden in his jacket pocket.

00:35:36.100 --> 00:35:40.910
In the late 1920's, retired banker,
Ben Tucker, and wife, Dorothy Mae,

00:35:40.910 --> 00:35:44.240
started feeding hummers on
their twelve acre property

00:35:44.240 --> 00:35:46.580
in Orange County, California.

00:35:46.580 --> 00:35:50.990
Here's Mr. Tucker in his
shop, building a bird house.

00:35:50.990 --> 00:35:55.280
But he built hummer feeders, too.

00:35:55.280 --> 00:36:00.400
The first ones were prohibition
era happy hour glasses with holes

00:36:00.400 --> 00:36:04.950
in tin lids just right
for hummingbirds.

00:36:04.950 --> 00:36:10.190
Local birders visited the Tucker's
famous outside hummingbird bar

00:36:10.190 --> 00:36:15.830
to sip cocktails and watch as many
as 200 hummingbirds at a time.

00:36:15.830 --> 00:36:21.090
An improved Tucker design was a
globe shaped chicken water fountain

00:36:21.090 --> 00:36:24.830
with a wire rail added
for hummer perching.

00:36:26.940 --> 00:36:31.110
This was a popular design
for a while created in 1928

00:36:31.110 --> 00:36:33.450
by the husband of Edith Webster.

00:36:33.450 --> 00:36:35.880
He used a glass mixing
tube from his lab

00:36:35.880 --> 00:36:40.380
at MIT an attached
open spouts on the end.

00:36:40.380 --> 00:36:45.530
Edith tasted all the flowers in
her New Hampshire yard to come

00:36:45.530 --> 00:36:50.460
up with a one part sugar
to two parts water recipe.

00:36:50.460 --> 00:36:54.800
Today's standard mix is one
part sugar to four parts water

00:36:54.800 --> 00:36:58.740
which is more like nectar flower.

00:37:00.660 --> 00:37:03.110
And today there are many new

00:37:03.110 --> 00:37:05.370
and different hummingbird
feeder designs.

