00:37:42.000 --> 00:37:49.510
But he had also worked on teaching
art work, engaging custom design,

00:37:49.510 --> 00:37:53.600
creating furniture,
high end furniture.

00:37:53.600 --> 00:37:55.620
He had a number of
industrial machines

00:37:55.620 --> 00:37:57.980
and received multiple patents.

00:37:57.980 --> 00:38:00.790
He was a kind of do-it-all fellow.

00:38:00.790 --> 00:38:05.580
His little company, launched
in 1960, Droll Yankees,

00:38:05.580 --> 00:38:12.630
was based at his wharf
situated workshop.

00:38:12.630 --> 00:38:15.930
And it basically had sold records.

00:38:15.930 --> 00:38:21.000
Some of you may remember
those round objects, records.

00:38:21.000 --> 00:38:22.740
They were novelty records.

00:38:22.740 --> 00:38:26.810
It included Yankee
storytelling and the recordings

00:38:26.810 --> 00:38:31.920
